<HEADLINE> Germany Strongly Condemns Jerusalem Bombings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Germany condemned the suicide
bombings in Jerusalem today as "a barbaric and cowardly act of
terrorism" and hoped that the Middle East peace process would not
be undermined.
</P>
<P>
German government spokesman Peter Hausmann made the remarks in
reaction to two suicide bombings at a crowded outdoor market in
Jewish West Jerusalem today, which killed at least 18 people and
injured over 150. He said Germany would continue to push for a
negotiated peace in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
In a condolence telegram to the Israeli government, German
Chancellor Helmut Kohl said, "I strongly condemn this malicious
act and hope that the will for peace and reconciliation in the
region will not be undermined." 
</P>
</TEXT>
