<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Violent Crime Rate Highest in UK Among European Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Britain has the highest rates of
violent crime, burglary and car theft among European countries,
according to a latest survey published today.
</P>
<P>
The International Crime Victimization Survey of 19,000 adults
in 11 countries including the UK, France, Sweden, Switzerland,
Finland and Austria, as well as Canada and the US revealed a
depressing picture of extremely high crime rates and fearfulness
among Britain's population.
</P>
<P>
The joint Home Office-funded study found that one in three
people in Britain have been a victim of crime, joint highest with
the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
With crimes involving robbery, assault and sexual assault, the
highest risks are also in Britain. Three percent of people in
Britain have had their cars stolen, the highest rate.
</P>
<P>
It is also highest for theft from cars, with about one in 10
people in Britain suffering a break in.
</P>
<P>
Britain comes second, only behind the Netherlands, when
examining comparative risks in terms of the number of crimes
experienced per citizen, with 61 offenses per 100 people.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Britain has slipped to having the highest
crime rate, from being sixth out of 15 countries in a 1989 survey.
</P>
</TEXT>
