<HEADLINE> PLO Official Attacks Netanyahu for Bombings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking official of the
Palestine Liberation Organization has held Israeli government
responsible for the two bomb blasts this afternoon in West
Jerusalem killing 14 people and wounding over 170.
</P>
<P>
Farouk Kaddoumi, director of the PLO Political Department, made
the accusation in a statement issued in Tunis after the suicide
bombings in a busy open-air market of Mahane Yehuda.
</P>
<P>
Kaddoumi said Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and his
government are directly responsible for poisoning the atmosphere
between Palestinians and Israelis, for freezing peace, and for the
eruption of such incidents.
</P>
<P>
"We have affirmed from the very outset our desire for peace,
and the Palestinian masses demonstrated in favor of the peace
process. They have even put flowers in gun barrels of Israeli
soldiers as an expression of their overwhelming support of peace,"
Kaddoumi said.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, "the racist Israeli government, ever since it
came to power, has perpetrated provocative acts against the
Palestinian people and has turned its back to the peace process
and to the singed agreements."
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian people are living until this very moment under
siege, suppression and terror, and are being denied the means of
dignified life, he pointed out. 
</P>
