<HEADLINE> Turkey Condemns Suicide Bombings in Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Turkey today strongly denounced the
suicide bombings in Jerusalem which killed at least 14 people and
wounded over 170 others.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here this evening, the Foreign Ministry
said "Those kind of terrorist actions, which are directed at the
living rights of people and aimed at killing innocent people
without making discrimination between them, neither gives any
advantage to the terrorists nor makes those actions right."
</P>
