only construe "an aggression against Israelis but also an attack
on the peace process as a whole, on the Palestinian National
Authority, the Palestinians and on Chairman Yasser Arafat."
</P>
<P>
"The purpose behind this incident is to torpedo the peace
process and smash the Palestinian government. It is important for
all of us to resume the peace process talks after the period of
mourning for the victims," he said.
</P>
<P>
When asked if the assault stemmed from a feeling of frustration
and desperation on the part of Palestinians over the freeze
in the peace process, the U.S. diplomat said there is "no excuse
justifying such an attack under any circumstance."
</P>
<P>
Palestinian-Israeli talks have been deadlocked for four months
over the Israeli decision to build thousands of new Jewish homes
in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton has condemned the suicide bombings
in Jerusalem and urged the Palestinian National Authority to take
more decisive steps to improve security.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Mideast envoy Dennis Ross postponed his planned mission to
the region until the mourning for the victims is over. Israel has
decided to suspend talks with Palestinians after the attack.
