<HEADLINE> Northeast China City Economy Rises 11.3 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Harbin, the capital city of
northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, saw its GDP rise 11.3
percent compared with the corresponding 1996 period, which is 1.8
percentage points higher than the national average, to 31.27
billion yuan during the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The city's non-state sector grew 14.9 percent and took up 55.1
percent of the city's total GDP, according to the city's
statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
The city further strengthened its trade with Russia during the
six-month period. Its foreign trade volume and utilization of
foreign investment both registered a rise of 23 percent on a
yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
