<HEADLINE> NATO Plays Key Role in Polish Flood Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) has been playing a key role in the Polish
flood relief work, a NATO press release said here today.
</P>
<P>
The military alliance has served as a switchboard between
the United Nations Department of Humanitarian Affairs and the
pre-designated emergency points of contact in NATO members and
countries in the Euro-Atlantic Partnership Council, the release
said.
</P>
<P>
NATO, which announced earlier this month to take in Poland,
Hungary and the Czech Republic as new members, has helped to seek
aid for rescue and recovery equipment such as pumps, generators
and water purifiers.
</P>
<P>
14 of the NATO and partner countries have responded by
providing financial assistance alongside the rescue and recovery
equipment to those locations in Poland in greatest need.
</P>
<P>
Successive heavy rains in Poland earlier this month submerged
some 621,000 hectares of land, of which a third is still under
water.
</P>
<P>
And at least 50,000 Poles have become homeless because of the
flood, according to Polish government spokesman Krzysztof Pomes.
</P>
</TEXT>
