<DOCNO> XIE19970731.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IAAF Reduces Drug-Ban From Four To Two Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The International Amateur Athletic
Federation (IAAF) reduced the suspension on drug-taking athletes
from four years to two here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The IAAF Congress voted by 112 to 56 for the move, although the
English and Canadian delegates strongly opposed the change.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed to end the automatic three months ban on
athletes caught taking stimulants. Instead they will be given a
public warning.
</P>
<P>
IAAF President Primo Nebiolo said the IAAF had to reduce the
punishment because of the threats of legal action from the United
States. Germany, Spain, France and Russia have refused to
implement the four-year ban.
</P>
<P>
The 74-year-old Nebiolo stressed that it was up to the
individual federations to decide whether to impose longer bans or
not if their national law allowed them to.
</P>
<P>
Attempts to have the ban reduced to two years at Gothenburg in
1995 failed but there has been growing pressure within the IAAF
to try and avoid costly court battles by halving the ban.
</P>
<P>
In a bid to crack down on cheating at least 300 dope tests will
be carried out during the upcoming World Championships which begin
here on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970731.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Issues Editorial To Mark Army's Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- China's leading newspaper, the
People's Daily, will carry an editorial tomorrow to mark the 70th
anniversary of the founding of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
The PLA is an armed group led by the Communist Party of China
to carry out revolutionary and political duties. It is also a
strong pillar of the people's democratic dictatorship and is
an important guarantee for national security, social stability and
the unification of the motherland, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 70 years, the PLA has adhered to the guidelines
and principles of the Communist Party of China and has played an
important role in overthrowing the three big mountains
(imperialism, feudalism and bureaucrat-capitalism, which weighed
like mountains on the backs of the Chinese people before
liberation), founding New China, safeguarding the sacred
territories of the motherland, protecting the socialist
modernization, reform and opening drive, and promoting the
peaceful reunification of the motherland and the realization of
the smooth return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The paper praises the PLA's participation in the country's
technological progress, industrial and agricultural production,
poverty-relief efforts and struggles against natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
The editorial calls on the army to adhere to Deng Xiaoping's
theory on army building and meet President Jiang Zemin's demand
that the troops "be qualified politically and competent
militarily, have a fine work style, be strictly disciplined and be
assured of adequate logistical support."
</P>
<P>
The principle that "the Party commands the gun" must be
followed, it stresses.
</P>
<P>
It emphasizes the need to improve the quality of the army and
step up its modernization drive, and to further reinforce the
unity between the army and the government, and the army and the
people. The relationship between economic and defense sectors must
be properly handled.
</P>
<P>
Peace and development are now the primary goals throughout the
world, but since hegemonism and power politics still exist, the
Chinese army must do more to modernize and standardize itself, the
editorial says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
