<HEADLINE> Zhuhai Special Economic Zone's Industry Grows 13.5 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Zhuhai Special Economic Zone
produced 16.936 billion yuan-worth of industrial products during
the first half of the year, 13.5 percent more than the same period
last year, according to the zone's statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
Investment demand rebounded during the six-month period after
two years of negative growth. Fixed assets investment rose 11.4
percent on a yearly basis to 3.28 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Construction on a 80,000-ton oil dock and storage unit and a
3.72 million-kilowatt power generating plant are going smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai was one of the four special economic zones approved by
the State Council in 1980. It borders Macao on the south and Hong
Kong on the east. 
</P>
