<HEADLINE> HK Share Prices Rise to New Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Stock Market
continued its surging momentum today with the Hang Seng Index
gaining 382 points, or 2.39 percent, to close at 16,365.
</P>
<P>
This is the market's third consecutive record-closing trading
day, and is also the first time for the Hang Seng Index to break
the 16,000-point barrier.
</P>
<P>
Trading on the market were especially active, with the total
turnover also reaching a record high of 28.033 billion HK dollars
(3.59 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Property stocks continued to lead the market. The properties
sub-index jumped 1,068 points, or 4.10 percent, to close at
27,116.
</P>
<P>
Of the other sub-indices, finance surged 402 points to 20,493;
commerce and industry rose 214 points to 10,717; and utilities
went up 101 points to 14,209.
</P>
<P>
In terms of growth percentage, Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index tops all the sub-indices with a 7 percent or 82 points rise
to close at 1,257.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Hong Kong Stock Market said the bullish
sentiment of the market is both normal and healthy.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region on July 1, the Hang Seng Index has set eight new closing
records in exactly one month.
</P>
<P>
Some local analysts say the market's growing mood will continue
for sometime, and there is still room for the Index to break
17,000 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
