<HEADLINE> HK Airport Railway Linked Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The railway connecting Hong
Kong's new airport at Chek Lap Kok and Hong Kong Island has been
linked up and the first works train arrived at the Island terminus
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 34-km-long railway is contracted for completion in June
1998, while the airport is due to open in April 1998.
</P>
<P>
A project director of the Mass Transit Railway Corporation, the
contractor, said the company is confident that it will be able to
accelerate the airport railway project to meet the opening date of
the airport if enough laborers are hired.
</P>
<P>
An Airport Authority spokesman said a firm opening date for the
new airport will be defined in September.
</P>
<P>
To date over 75 percent of the railway project is complete,
with civil construction work almost over and electrical and
mechanical works under way at all stations.  
</P>
