<HEADLINE> Shandong-Thai Textile Company Listed On Shenzhen Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Shandong-Thai Textile
Co. Ltd., one of China's leading textiles manufacturers, began to
issue B shares on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange today.
</P>
<P>
The company will offer 80 million B shares at a price of 2.065
yuan (1.932 HK dollars) per share. Profits will be primarily used
to expand yarn-dyed cloth production.
</P>
<P>
The company is a joint venture between Shandong, in east China,
and Thailand. Its major products include cotton-polyester blended
yarn, dyed cloth, and underwear. Nearly 70 percent of the products
are exported to Japan, the Republic of Korea and Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The company's sales are expected to hit 303 million yuan and
after-tax profits 37.5 million yuan by the end of this year, an
increase of 50 percent and 23 percent, respectively, over last
year.
</P>
<P>
A development program up to the year 2000 calls for production
capacity for cotton yarn to climb to 3,200 tons and dyed cloth to
22 million meters. 
</P>
