<HEADLINE> 2 Killed in PKK Attack in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A Turkish sergeant and a village
guard were killed today in an attack launched by the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in southeastern Turkey, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
A group of PKK militants exchanged fire with Turkish security
forces this morning when the group staged the attack on Gecitli
village in Hakkari province.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the security forces have besieged a
mountainous area to which the PKK guerrillas escaped after the
attack.
</P>
<P>
In another development, some PKK rebels launched rockets on
Karsilar village in southeastern province of Tunceli late
Wednesday night, killing one villager and wounding three
others.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the agency reported that two children were killed
when a mine planted by the PKK rebels exploded near a river in
Gurpinar town of Van province.
</P>
<P>
Over 27,000 people, including PKK militants, civilians and
government troops have been killed in conflicts since the PKK
started a separatist war for autonomy in eastern and southeastern
Turkey in August 1984. 
</P>
