<HEADLINE> Army Should Stick to Deng's Socialist Theory: Jiang (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Army (PLA)
must hold the banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics high, Chinese president
Jiang Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and chairman of the Central
Military Commission (CMC), made the remark at a rally in Beijing's
Great Hall of the People to mark the 70th anniversary of the PLA,
where he said that China is witnessing an important historical
period of continuing the reforms, opening up, and the
modernization drive as the 21st century approaches.
</P>
<P>
"We must have a powerful army and consolidate our national
defense in order to safeguard unity and the safety of the country
and to promote world peace and stability," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The army must maintain a clear view of both the domestic and
international situations, he said, urging the army to be vigilant
in peace time, and strengthen their sense of responsibility and
mission, and launch a full-scale military development effort.
</P>
<P>
We must endeavor to create a new phase of the army's
revolutionization, modernization, and regularization in accordance
with the overall needs of being qualified politically and
competent militarily, having a fine style of work, being strictly
disciplined and being assured of adequate logistic support, he
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
