<DOCNO> XIE19970731.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Army Should Stick to Deng's Socialist Theory: Jiang (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After recalling the PLA's history, Jiang said that the 70-year
history has proven that the PLA is loyal to the Party and the
people, and has the courage to overcome all difficulties and to
overpower all enemies. The PLA is an army with lofty ideals, moral
integrity, a good education, and strong sense of discipline.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized that the reason the PLA has become a great
army is that it has always abided by the basic principle of the
Party's absolute leadership. It is an armed force that has
fulfilled political tasks assigned by the Party, stood firmly on
the Party's side, receiving orders from the Party since the day it
was established, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"The idea of the Party's absolute leadership over the army has
taken root in all officers and soldiers," he noted, adding that a
system has been formed that guarantees the Party's absolute
leadership over the army.
</P>
<P>
Party committees at all levels in the armed forces have played
a leadership role. Grass-roots party branches have acted as
fighting forces. The CPC members have played the role of vanguard
and model. "All of these have made the PLA a battle-tested
militant collective," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The CPC will draw up a strategic plan for major issues like
reforms, development, and stability at the forthcoming 15th
National Congress of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
"Our future is bright, and our tasks are both glorious and
arduous," said Jiang. "Let's be closely united and make an effort
to build our country into a prosperous and strong, democratic,
civilized and modernized socialist country, and build our army
into a powerful, modernized and regularized revolutionary army,
under the guidance of Deng's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics and the basic principles of the Party."
</P>
</TEXT>
