<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar finished
weaker today following the release of the retail sales figures by
the Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS).
</P>
<P>
The local unit finished at 74.34 US cents, from 74.61 locally
late Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The ABS said retail trade fell a seasonally adjusted 1.8
percent in June, compared to expectations of a 0.3 percent rise in
the month.
</P>
<P>
"The fall after the data was announced indicated the market may
have been prompting another rate cut," a dealer said.
</P>
<P>
However, economists cautioned further economic data signaling
sluggish growth and a stalled labor market was needed before
speculation of another rate cut could be taken seriously.
</P>
<P>
The Reserve Bank of Australia Wednesday cut the cash rate to
5.0 percent from 5.5, citing an improved outlook for inflation.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was at 87.61 Japanese yen, from 88.48
yen, and at 1.3648 German marks, from 1.3718 marks.  
