<HEADLINE> EU to Stage All-Star Soccer Games Against Racism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Superstars George Weah, Eric
Cantona and Diego Maradona will lead their likes from around the
world in three exhibition games slated for mid-October as part of
the activities of the European Year Against Racism.
</P>
<P>
The 40-minute games will be organized by the International
Football Association (FIFA) in cooperation with the European
Commission, the executive body of the European Union, it was
learned here today.
</P>
<P>
Weah, Cantona and Maradona will each captain an all-star team
in a round-robin tournament to be held in Spain starting on
October 12 this year.
</P>
<P>
Padraig Flynn, European Commissioner in charge of social
affairs, said in a press release that the tournament will bring
together some of the world's best football players united in their
determination to show that racism has no place in the society.
</P>
<P>
Weah was chosen as the 1995 world footballer of the year while
Cantona paced Manchester United to two English premiere league
championship triumphs.
</P>
<P>
Maradona, though disgraced by his failure of doping test at the
1994 World Cup tournament in the United States, has been held as a
national hero as he led Argentina to win the 1986 World Cup title
in Mexico. 
