<HEADLINE> Chinese Army Being Streamlined To Produce More Efficient Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin said here
today that cutting the numbers and improving the quality of the
People's Liberation Army (PLA) is a basic principle of its
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party and chairman of the
Central Military Commission, made the remarks at a gathering
marking the 70th anniversary of the founding of the PLA today.
</P>
<P>
Streamlining the army with Chinese characteristics is the right
choice for China in military modernization, he said, emphasizing
that quality is an international trend with technology being
widely used in the military and that the Chinese army should have
a policy of quality improvement in all respects.
</P>
<P>
"Officers and soldiers should learn more about technology and
modern warfare," he said, and that the structure of the army
should be improved in line with strategic principles in the new
era and that training of soldiers and military and other college
students should be reformed .
</P>
<P>
Management of the army should be improved so that the army will
be better disciplined. And as for the relationship between
modernizing the military and economic construction, the country
should focus on economic development and the modernization of the
military forces give support to that.
</P>
<P>
With a growing economy, Jiang said, the country will increase
investment in national defence, improving military equipment and
the army's living standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
