<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tung Underlines Two Crucial Factors for HK Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), today
underlined the rule of law and the free market economy as two
"critical success factors" for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a luncheon give by the Australian Chamber of
Commerce at the Grand Hyatt Hotel, Tung stressed that the rule of
law must be preserved by all means and it will be preserved by all
 means.
</P>
<P>
"All that I do, all the (Hong Kong SAR) government does, must
be and will be in accordance with the law, because we know that
the rule of law is essential to the continued success of Hong
Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
Touching on another crucial factor for Hong Kong's success --
the free market economy, Tung said: "We let the market take the
lead in setting its own parameters while government intervention
is kept to a minimum."
</P>
<P>
"We have some of the world's largest foreign currency reserves,
 we have the busiest container port in the world and the busiest
international air freight throughput," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Hong Kong has an annual Gross Domestic Product
(GDP) per capita higher than many Western nations.
</P>
<P>
"One of the major reasons for our remarkable economic success
is undoubtedly Hong Kong's industrious, flexible and skilled
workforce," Tung said. "This, combined with our entrepreneurial
spirit, has enabled a gradual and smooth shift from a
manufacturing-based economy to one based on the provision of
services."
</P>
<P>
Tung also stressed that the Hong Kong SAR government has a
responsibility to ensure those, who cannot help themselves, live a
 decent and dignified life. It also must help those, who can help
themselves, with on-the-job training and help them to learn new
skills to meet the demands of the market, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
