<HEADLINE> Tung Reviews Hong Kong's First Month After Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), said today
that the past month had been "very important" for Hong Kong as its
 people became the masters of their own destiny for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a luncheon given by the Australian Chamber of
Commerce at the Grand Hyatt Hotel, Tung pointed out that today is
a small milestone for Hong Kong, since it marks the end of the
first month of existence of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
"This past month has been very important for Hong Kong and its
people because it has given us a chance to actually put into
practice those concepts about which we have heard so much -- that
is 'one country, two systems' and 'Hong Kong people ruling Hong
Kong,'" he said.
</P>
<P>
He said there had been no big change in Hong Kong since the
handover on July 1. "It is business as usual."
</P>
<P>
"What has changed is that Hong Kong has become a part of China
and there is immense pride that this has happened," he added.
</P>
<P>
There is "immense confidence" that Hong Kong's tomorrow will be
 even better, Tung said. He stressed the importance of maintaining
 and building Hong Kong's role as an international trade and
finance center and the need to make further efforts to ensure the
continued success of Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
