<HEADLINE> Reception For PLA's 70th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- National Defense Minister Chi
Haotian, who presided over a reception marking the 70th
anniversary of the  People's Liberation Army (PLA) in the Great
Hall of the People today, told the gathering that the PLA will
always strictly follow the commands of the Central Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) and those of the Central
Military Commission (CMC).
</P>
<P>
China's party and government leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao
Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong
Yiren, as well as over 1,700 people attended the reception held by
the Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is also vice-chairman of the CMC and state councillor,
said, "We will stand firm with the CPC with Jiang Zemin at its
core both in thought and action," and "We must never lose our
loyalty to the Party, to the motherland, to the people and to
socialism. We should serve the people heart and soul and never
change the nature of the people's army."
</P>
<P>
He recalled the PLA's glorious history from the struggle for
national independence and liberation to the founding of new China
and the country's reforms and opening up to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
"History has shown that without the CPC armed with scientific
theory, there would be no flourishing socialist China today," he
said, "And without a people's army under the leadership of the
CPC, the people would not have what they have today."
</P>
<P>
He said that the PLA garrison in Hong Kong must fulfill its
responsibilities in strict accordance with the Basic Law of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region and the Garrison Law, and
that it will actively contribute to maintaining the long-term
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
On the question of Taiwan, Chi said that China is committed to
settling that issue in line with the "peaceful reunification and
one country, two systems" principle.
</P>
<P>
"But we will never commit ourselves to forsaking the use of
force," he said, explaining that, "This is to preempt the forces
in Taiwan seeking Taiwan independence and splitting the motherland
and foreign intervention." 
</P>
</TEXT>
