<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flu Strikes Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A wave of influenza has struck Macao
 as hundreds of people went to see doctors over the past few days.
</P>
<P>
A report in today's Macao Daily News says that many people have
 complained of fever with body temperature as high as 39 degrees
Celsius. They also had headache and coughed.
</P>
<P>
The King Wu Hospital, one of the two leading hospitals in
Macao, accepted 123 patients with flu Monday. Many were of one
family or workers on the same assembly line.
</P>
<P>
Local doctors have warned citizens to pay attention to symptoms
 of flu and see doctors immediately for help. Delay can cause
other deadly diseases for weak patients.
</P>
<P>
They also said that while enjoying the cool in air-conditioned
rooms, people should open their windows some time to allow air
flow. Those who stay long time in closed rooms are prone to catch
the disease.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
