<HEADLINE> Triple Olympic Champion Smith to Compete In "Skins" Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Irish triple Olympic gold
medalist swimmer Michelle Smith will compete in a lucrative
"skins" event, Australian swimming officials said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The one-day meeting is due to be held in Sydney on August 30.
</P>
<P>
Smith made a big splash in the pool at last year's Centennial
Olympic Games in Atlanta. She collected two individual medley
events and the 400 meters freestyle at the Georgia Aquatic Center.
</P>
<P>
Smith has agreed to compete in Sydney, six days after the end
of the European Championships in Spain.
</P>
<P>
Other big shots that also comfirmed they entries included
Australians Susie O'Neill and Samantha Riley, American Gary Hall
Jnr and Finland's Jani Sievinen.
</P>
<P>
Under the "skins" rules, swimmers in each event compete in a
series of elimination races until just one competitor is left.
</P>
<P>
The 12 events carry a total prize money of 74,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
