<HEADLINE> 48 People Feared Drowned in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A total of 48 people were feared
drowned when a private luxury bus plunged into Narmada river in
Madhya Pradesh's Dewas district today.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the bus was proceeding towards
Indore city, 806 km south of New Delhi, capital of India, when the
mishap occurred.
</P>
<P>
Rescue operations are under way and the death toll could go up.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, over 100 people were drowned due to boat
and bus accidents in Bihar and Uttar Pradesh.  
</P>
