<HEADLINE> Rotary International Aids Nepal in Polio Vaccination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Rotary International has
agreed to provide the Nepali government with 300,000 U.S. dollars
for polio vaccination, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali government has declared December 7 this year and
January 18 next year as National Immunization Days.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, about 3.7 million children under age five in
Nepal will be administered free the polio vaccines.
</P>
<P>
Nepal is the only country after Yemen which has yet to complete
polio immunization, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The government has committed to eradicate polio by 2000 as
called upon by the World Health Organization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
