<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Two Palestinians transformed into human bombs killed 14
people Wednesday in a Jewish marketplace in Jerusalem. The
attack, claimed by the Hamas militant movement, came at the moment
when Israel and the Palestinian authority were preparing to resume
peace talks which were interrupted for four months.
</P>
<P>
-- According to newly declassified information of the United
States government, the Swiss bank Credit Suisse helped finance
German Nazis during World War II by paying money to a German
espionage station house in Basle, Switzerland. The money was used
to buy Swiss-made military materials for the Third Reich.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- A scenary of horror and panic prevailed at a big Jewish
marketplace in Jerusalem Wednesday as 14 people were killed and
more than 150 wounded in a double bombing attack. This is the
most bloody bombing attack in Israel since Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu came to power.
</P>
<P>
-- A team of experts headed by Patrick Weil will present today
a report to Prime Minister Lionel Jospin on the reform of France's
immigration law and code of nationality, which will serve as the
basis for two bills on immigration and nationality to be discussed
by parliament in autumn. The Weil report suggests a reinforcement
of the natural right of soil for children born in France of
foreign parents, but it does not require the abrogation of two
previous immigration laws adopted under two former interior
ministers Charles Pasqua and Jean-Louis Debre. 
</P>
</TEXT>
