<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman Condemns Explosion in Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang
Guoqiang, when asked to comment on the explosion in Jerusalem
yesterday, condemned the terrorist activities.
</P>
<P>
"We are deeply shocked at the explosion that occurred in
Jerusalem on July 30, and we express our heartfelt sympathy and
solicitude to those innocent victims and their relatives," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tang emphasized that the Chinese government opposes and
condemns terrorist activities of any kind, and calls on concerned
parties in the Middle East to keep calm and to use restraint, to
treasure the opportunity for peace which has not easily come by,
and to restore the peace talks as soon as possible to realize
peace and stability in the region at an early date. 
</P>
