<HEADLINE> Share Prices Almost Steady on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Share prices almost stayed
steady on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index rose 0.73 points to close at 1967.14 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume increased to 160.72 million units, valued
at 395.08 million Singapore dollars (about 270.6 million U.S.
dollars). Declines continued to overwhelm advances by 233 to 96,
while 283 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Local computer maker IPC Corporation was the most actively
traded stock for the second day running as it posted a turnover of
18.51 million units. It was followed by Asia Food &AMP; Properties
which had 16.69 million shares traded. The Hong Kong Land was next
with 9.27 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose 1.1 Singapore dollars to finish at 27.9
Singapore dollars. The United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign gained
60 cents to end at 16 Singapore dollars. Venture closed 50 cents
higher at seven dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 and the Development Bank of
Singapore (DBS) Foreign shared the top spot on the losers' list as
each of them declined 60 cents to end at 31.2 and 19.1 Singapore
dollars respectively. City Developments fell 40 cents to close at
12.5 Singapore dollars, while F&AMP;N finished 30 cents lower at ten
Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
