<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's CBC Expands Foreign Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- China Construction Bank (CBC) has
witnessed soaring growth in foreign business since redoubling its
efforts to develop international settlements and investment
banking.
</P>
<P>
A recent bank report shows foreign exchange earnings jumped
34.86 million US dollars to 125.66 million US dollars for the
first half of the year, up 38 percent on last year's period.
</P>
<P>
CBC's international settlement volume surged ahead 47.6 percent
to 22.56 billion US dollars, up 7.28 billion US dollars from the
same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Foreign exchange deposits for the period climbed 8.94 percent
to 6.651 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The bank also registered marked growth in purchases and sales
of foreign exchange, with the total volume for the period soaring
71.7 percent, or 5.2 billion US dollars to 12.422 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Investment banking has emerged as a new growth area, and the
bank has successfully taken full advantage of its long-term
participated in both major projects and foreign exchange
projects by providing financial consulting, arranging investments
and guaranteeing major infrastructure projects in diverse areas
such as public utilities.
</P>
<P>
The bank trebled funds raised for the period to 1.37 billion US
dollars, with the influx of funds coming from wide-ranging
channels, including foreign government loans, export seller's
credits, commercial loans and bonds floatations.
</P>
<P>
CBC has opened seven foreign branches and representative
offices, and has established correspondent banking relations with
600 banks worldwide.  
</P>
</TEXT>
