<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Film Studio in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in east China's coastal
province of Zhejiang have backed what is said to be Asia's biggest
film studio.
</P>
<P>
The Hengdian Group, a township cement enterprise in rural
Dongyang County, spent tens of millions of yuan on a film city for
shooting "The Opium War", directed by one of China's most famous
directors, Xie Jin.
</P>
<P>
The film city has a 'Guangzhou Street of the 19th century' with
more than 160 buildings that reflect the flavor of south China in
the 1800s.
</P>
<P>
Bamianshan Film City has become a popular spot for film
directors since Xie chose it for his blockbuster.
</P>
<P>
The owners of the film city are adding a Beijing Imperial
Palace, ancient Beijing streets, Japanese and Hong Kong streets,
and places from the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The tourists from both China and overseas are able to travel to
the places they have seen on film. By the end of June, 'Guangzhou
Street of the 19th century' had received hundreds of thousands of
visitors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
