<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Technology Promoting Root Growth In Plants Helps Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The use of a new root-growth
enhancing powder on 6,700 hectares of arable land in Shanghai area
has helped add 1.38 million kg of grain products, or more than 20
million yuan (2.5 million US dollars) in value, according to the
Municipal Academy of Agricultural Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The ABT Series Plant Root-Promotion Powder was invented by Wang
Tao of the Chinese Academy of Forestry Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Tests have shown that by using the powder, the survival rate of
young trees can be increased by some 15 percent, and the output of
various crops can be increased from seven to 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The powder has won a top state prize for science and technology
and has been found effective for vegetables like cucumbers,
celery, and tomatoes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
