<HEADLINE> CITS Serves More Foreign Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The China International Travel
Service (CITS), China's largest travel agency, provided services
to 243,000 foreign tourists between January-June, up 13.2 percent
on last year's period.
</P>
<P>
European tourists account for 34.2 percent of the total
number of foreign tour groups, with significant increases also
recorded for tourists from the United States, Canada,
and Latin America.
</P>
<P>
The number of Asian tourists remained at the same level, with a
drop in the number of people arriving from Oceania.
</P>
<P>
CITS expects the number of tourists in 1997 to rise by
some 10 percent due the increasingly fierce competition on the
foreign market.
</P>
<P>
The agency recorded increasing profits, with total earnings
rising 7.5 percent on the 1996 period to 573 million yuan.
</P>
</TEXT>
