<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Views on Science Fiction  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Followers of science fiction say the writing form is grabbing
the attention of more and more Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Guangzhao, president of the China Association for Science
and Technology, said that the most influential technological
innovations and inventions introduced during the 20th century have
evolved from the imaginative descriptions created by science
fiction writers.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Wenguang, father of Chinese contemporary science fiction,
claimed that sci-fi writers have the responsibility to develop the
literary form so as to attract not only children but adults.
</P>
<P>
China's only sci-fi magazine, "Science Fiction World," has a
readership of approximately 300,000, the largest among all the
publications of its kind in the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
"The popularity of the magazine shows the change in Chinese
people's mentality," said Wu Yan, member of the Chinese Writers'
Association.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of science fiction, Wu noted, is not only to spread
scientific knowledge, but also to "provide humanistic background
for readership to think over the impact of scientific development
on culture and deeper layers of the society."
</P>
<P>
In his new story which fictionalizes the history of the Chinese
sending mankind into outer space, Wu showed how a weak nation like
China survives by struggle and self-sacrifice.
</P>
<P>
Some Chinese people believe that science fiction can predict
potential crises that may result from scientific development.
</P>
<P>
A story about the cloning of human beings published in China
last year mentioned the dangers of the technology. It has aroused
widespread concern among some natural and social scientists who
consider that many of the details in the story are similar those
of the recent sheep cloning experiments in Britain.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese people are now displaying a serious and earnest
attitude towards science fiction," said Yang Xiao, chief editor of
"Science Fiction World."
</P>
<P>
She said that science fiction is a new form of literature for
people with a modern mindset, and will be the mainstream
literature of the 21st century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
