<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
was stable today with the market indicator closing slightly lower
in heavy trunover.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 3 points lower at 2,573 with a turnover
of 93 million NZ dollars (60 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Leaders which fell included Carter Holt Harvey, dipping 6 cents
to 375 cents, Fletcher Paper, easing 4c to 350c, and Telecom,
slipping 3c to 785c. Air New Zealand was also weaker, losing 1c to
314c.
</P>
<P>
Leaders going against the weaker trend were Lion Nathan,
gaining 3c to 400c, and Brierley Investment, rising 1c to 141c.
</P>
<P>
But the broader market showed strength with rises outnumbering
falls by 60 to 45 and the smaller companies index up almost 18
points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
