<HEADLINE> First Silk Atlas Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai-based "Wenhui Daily"
reports that China is preparing to hold its first auction of silk
atlases produced using computerized colorization on August 3.
</P>
<P>
The successful production of the atlases has been certified in
the Guiness Book of World Records.
</P>
<P>
Negatives for the 16-map 1996 version colorized atlases were
destroyed on July 29 under the supervision of the Shanghai
Notarization Office.
</P>
<P>
Only 200 editions of the aforementioned silk atlases remain on
the market, and destruction of the negatives prevents the
possibility of any further production.
</P>
<P>
The Qiyin Silk Corp. has announced that it will print and
auction 1997 versions of the World Atlas and China Atlas following
the destruction of negatives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
