<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China City Builds Science Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- China's first energy sciences park
is currently under construction in the Yintan Tourist Area, Rushan
City, east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The park's eight museums will feature exhibitions of
wide-ranging subjects, including wind, geothermal and hydrogen
energy, as well as scientific and technological exchanges and
various related areas.
</P>
<P>
The wind and solar energy museums will be completed by the end
of this year at a cost of four million yuan (482,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The park will introduce the development history, basic theories
and application chronology of various kinds of new and renewable
energy resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
