<HEADLINE> 23 Workers Killed in Stampede in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- At least 23 garment workers, mostly
women, died and more than 100 others injured in a stampede caused
by a minor fire at a garment factory in Dhaka on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said that a large number of panicked workers chocked
the exit following the fire which was caused by short circuit in
the switch board of the garment factory.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the exit was made more difficult to pass through
as the guard had reportedly kept the main gate closed partly to
bar the entry of outsiders in view of the day's industrial strike
and to prevent the workers from leaving their workplace during
duty hours.
</P>
<P>
Six policemen were also injured when the angry people attacked
them with bricks and stones as they were trying to remove the
bodies of the victims from the spot.
</P>
<P>
This is the second tragic incident in garment factories within
two weeks in the same area. 
</P>
