<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Herbal Foot Dressing Treatment for Mumps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Li Xinmin, a doctor in Guiyang,
capital of southwest China's Guizhou Province, uses herbal foot
dressings to treat parotitis (mumps).
</P>
<P>
Children are especially susceptible to parotitis, a highly
infectious disease Chinese refer to as "Monkey Lumps".
</P>
<P>
Western doctors prefer to treat parotitis with
anti-inflammatory drugs or incisions to facilitate drainage, while
doctors of traditional Chinese medicine opt for the use of herbal
foot dressings.
</P>
<P>
Li developed his therapy based on a prescription handed down
through generations of his family. The procedure involves applying
a bag of herbal medicine soaked with vinegar to an acupoint on the
sole of a patient's foot.
</P>
<P>
The herbal medicine takes effect in 24 hours and a patient
fully recovers within two days.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, "the therapy is based on the traditional
Chinese medical theory that upper body ailments can be treated by
stimulating acupoints in the lower extremities".
</P>
<P>
Li have used the procedure to successfully treat well over
1,000 patients in the past 20 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970731.0172 </DOCNO>
