<HEADLINE> Grote Sets Year's Best in 200 Meters Breaststroke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Kurt Grote set the world's
fastest time of the year in the men's 200-meter breaststroke at
the U.S. Swimming Nationals in Nashville, Tennessee on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Grote completed a sweep of the meet's two
breaststroke events Wednesday night with a career best of two
minutes 12.35 seconds in the 200 meters.
</P>
<P>
Grote, who won the 100 breaststroke earlier this week,
shortened nearly four seconds off his morning qualifying time in
the 200 final for the third fastest time by an American in the
event and eighth fastest ever in the world.
</P>
<P>
In other finals Wednesday, Olympian Kristine Quance won
the 200-meter individual medley in a personal best of 2:13.55.
</P>
<P>
She has now qualified for the world championships in the
200 and 400 individual medley and 100-meter breaststroke.
</P>
<P>
Neil Walker won the 100-meter butterfly in a career best time
of 53.06 after injuring his left hand in March this year.
</P>
