<HEADLINE> Hamas Claims Responsibility for Suicide Bombings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The armed wing of the Islamic
Resistance Movement (Hamas) claimed responsibility for Wednesday's
double suicide-bombing attack in Jewish west Jerusalem's central
open market, which killed 13 Israelis and wounded 168.
</P>
<P>
In a leaflet posted near the International Red Cross office in
the West Bank city of Ramallah, Hamas also demanded the release by
9 p.m. Sunday of its spiritual leader Sheikh Ahmed Yassin,
Hezbollah leader Sheikh Abdul Karim Obeid, and other security
prisoners and administrative detainees.
</P>
<P>
But the leaflet failed to mention what it would do when the
deadline expires.
</P>
<P>
The leaflet said that the bombing attack was "a present from
Mohammad's soldiers in response to the satanic leaflet that the
pigs distributed in Hebron," an apparent reference to the
leaflets depicting the Prophet Mohammad as a pig posted by an
Israeli woman in Hebron last month. 
