<HEADLINE> Sexual Offenses Increase in Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The number of rape cases in
Nicaragua reached 753 in the first half of the year, more than the
566 cases in 1996, a senior police officer said today.
</P>
<P>
In 213 of the rape cases reported from January to June, the
victims were students or housewives, said Gerardo Arce, chief of
the National Police Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Many victims were minors who, apart from the physical abuse,
would grow up with emotional traumas, Arce said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the total rape cases could be up to 2,000 this
year.
</P>
<P>
The first six months of the year also saw 774 cases of abuse,
obscenity and harassment in Nicaragua, he said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,037 sexual offenses were recorded in 1995, hitting
5 in every 10,000 people of the country's population. And it took
on 6.4 in every 10,000 people in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
