<HEADLINE> Ukraine Seeking Close Ties With Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma
indicated at a meeting with German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel
today that his country may seek entry into the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Ukraine is determined to enhance strategic cooperation with
Europe and trans-Atlantic organizations, said Ukrainian Foreign
Minister Gennady Udovenko after his own talks with Kinkel.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko told a press conference that the EU-Ukrainian summit
slated on September 5 in Luxembourg will be no less significant
than the special partership charter between Ukraine and NATO.
</P>
<P>
On his part, the German foreign minister, who is scheduled to
end his two-day stay here today, told reporters that his country
backs Ukraine's ongoing economic and democratic reforms.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel hailed Ukraine's diplomatic achievements in recent
months, saying that European nations and the EU regard the former
Soviet republic as a special friend instead of a buffer zone.
</P>
<P>
Germany, which set up a representative office in the Ukrainian
capital of Kiev in 1989, is one of the first Western countries to
realize Ukraine's importance for the world, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
