<HEADLINE> Yantai Development Zone Attracts More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Yantai Economic and Technological
Development Zone, one of such zones established along with China's
opening-up drive in the middle 1980s, attracted foreign
investments of well over 75 million US dollars during the first
half of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Management committee director Yan Yuantian said the
investments were used to fund 29 new industrial projects in the
zone in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The zone's foreign-funded enterprises recorded a total
industrial output value of two billion yuan during the first six
months of this year, up 62.2 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Yan also noted the import-export trade volume in the
development zone also jumped by 38.5 percent to over 200 million
US dollars. 
