<HEADLINE> 20 Injured in Sri Lanka's Student Demonstration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- About 20 persons were injured
Wednesday evening when police broke up a student demonstration
here using tear-gas, water cannon and rubber bullets, police said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Students from the Inter University Students Federation (IUSF)
were demonstrating on the opposite side of Colombo's main railway
station in protest against education reforms which are being
discussed in the educational sector.
</P>
<P>
According to police sources, the crowd numbering about 3,000
became unruly and blocked the road. Police then fired tear gas
canisters and used water cannon to disperse the crowd.
</P>
<P>
The crowd retaliated by throwing missiles back at police who
were compelled to take sterner action, charging the crowd with
batons.
</P>
<P>
About 20 persons were injured and admitted to hospital.
</P>
<P>
Buddhist monks, university students and school children were
among the injured. Several shops in the vicinity were damaged.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued last night, the IUSF said it wanted
to warn the country against the dangers of the reforms which can
not meet the needs of the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
