<HEADLINE> Joint Command Formed Against Cholera in Caracas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's health authorities
have set up what they call a "joint command" to fight cholera and
dengue fever in the Metropolitan Caracas area.
</P>
<P>
The command includes personnel from the health, defense and
interior ministries, the Federal District, the state of Miranda,
municipal halls and the Venezuelan Social Security Institute.
</P>
<P>
The move is prompted by the recent outbreak of cholera in the
metropolitan area, where 46 cases and three related deaths have
been registered since June 3, and six deaths so far this year.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, there were 66 cholera cases and three deaths in
this capital in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Besides, dengue fever has been epidemic in Caracas since the
beginning of this decade, and there have been 490 cases and three
related deaths this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
