<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A ship wreckage, apparently from
World War II, has been found by fishermen in the waters east of
Halmahera Island of Indonesia, the Antara News Agency reported
today.
</P>
<P>
"The ship found between Worg Island and Halmahera is strongly
presumed to belong to the Japanese imperial navy during World War
II," a villager was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
