that the drive will cost about 2.2 million U.S Dollars.
</P>
<P>
SADC plans to use the new technology to spot land mines laid
during conflicts and determine a precise figure of the explosive
devices in Southern Africa,the official was quoted by the local
press as saying.
</P>
<P>
Mbuende describes the exercise as a systematic cleaning
campaign to be carried out in such countries as Angola and
Mozambique, which are among the most heavily-mined countries in
the world.
</P>
<P>
SADC, comprising 12 Southern African countries, was formed in
1992 in Windhoek, Namibia, to lead the region to a free trade
zone by the year 2000. 
