<HEADLINE> 70th Anniversary of PLAC Exhibition Opened in Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 30 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition marking the 70th
anniversary of the People's Liberation Army of China (PLAC) opened
here in the Central Museum of the Armed Forces today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Military, Naval and Air
Attache of the Chinese embassy Maj. Gen. Feng Yuqiang emphasized
that China will never participate in the arms race, never conduct
military expansion and never seek hegemony."
</P>
<P>
General Vladimir Verevkin-Rahalisky, first vice-chairman of the
Russian War Veterans Committee, in his congratulatory speech
praised the PLAC for its glorious history and way, and said it is
very good that the time of frigid ties between the two countries
has gone.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the relations between Russia and
China as well as the ties between the two armies will be
strengthened and developed further.
</P>
<P>
On display at the exhibition were more than 50 photographs and
about 30 objects, which introduce the founding of the PLAC, its
way of defending the motherland and maintaining the order of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Attended the opening ceremony were about 200 people including
Russian military officers and veterans as well as military
attaches from the embassies of the United States, Britain, France,
Germany, Japan, Israel, Bulgaria, Poland, Yugoslavia, the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea, Vietnam, Laos, Myanmar,
India and other states.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, organized by the Martial Museum of China
(Beijing) and the Central Museum of the Armed Forces of Russia, is
expected to last a week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
