<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Jordan condemned today the two
suicide bombings in the West Jerusalem, which killed 14 people
and wounded over 170 others, as "terrorist" activity against the
innocent people, Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
The extremists committed the crime as hopeful signs just
emerged for the resumption of the Middle East peace process,
said a Jordanian government spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The attack was designed to further strain people's aspirations
for security, stability and prosperity in the peaceful Middle
East, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Incentives should be given to resume the peace negotiations
and revive the peace process to prevent the enemies of peace from
achieving their objectives, he added.
