<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US House Approves Balanced-budget Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. House of
Representatives approved today a legislation to balance the U.S.
budget over five years and the bill moved toward final passage in
the Senate.
</P>
<P>
The bill, which was approved by a vote of 346-85, designed to
rid the nation of deficits for the first time since 1969. U.S.
President Bill Clinton has pledged to sign it.
</P>
<P>
In all, the measure would curtail future spending by about 130
billion dollars over five years, thus helping balance the budget
in 2002, the first time in nearly 30 years.
</P>
<P>
Much of the savings in the balanced-budget bill would come from
Medicare, largely in the form of a squeeze on payments to doctors,
hospitals and other health care providers. Other savings are
anticipated from Medicaid, and, to a lesser degree, veterans
programs, student loans and other benefit programs.
</P>
<P>
A companion bill to cut taxes by about 150 billion dollars over
five years was next on the agenda for U.S. lawmakers. The measure
would cut taxes for families with children, students and investors
targeted. The bill will also increase tax by about 60 billion
dollars in the next five years. The measure was expected to breeze
to final passage in both houses before week's end.
</P>
<P>
Some U.S. lawmakers have opposed the tax measure. Tobacco state
lawmakers said they were unhappy with a provision raising the
tobacco tax, and some conservatives were expected to oppose the
child health program -- one of the features Democrats liked the
best.
</P>
<P>
A Senate vote on the balanced-budget bill was expected either
later today or Thursday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. government and Republican-controlled Congress reached an
agreement in May to balance the U.S. budget by 2002 by cutting
spending and tax. The balanced-budget bill will end the two years
and an half fierce struggle between the two U.S. parties on
whether and how to balance the U.S. budget. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970731.0262 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
