<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Ten high school band students
were killed in a crash between a tractor-trailer and a utility
vehicle when the vehicle was trying to pass in a no-passing zone
on a wet country road in North Carolina today.
</P>
<P>
The vehicle driver lost control after crossing the center line
to pass three cars in a light rain in an area about 170 kilometers
east of Raleigh, local media reports quoted police as saying.
</P>
<P>
The victims belonged to the Plymouth High School band and were
taking a lunch break from summer band camp at the school. Nine of
the ten students died on the spot and the only student to survive
the 1:30 p.m. crash died later at a hospital.
</P>
<P>
The truck driver was treated for minor injuries at a hospital
and released.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, two adults and nine children under 12 were killed
in southern Michigan when their pickup truck rolled past a stop
sign and was crushed by a dump truck. Two other children were
critically injured. 
</P>
