<HEADLINE> Prospected Modern Pentathlon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Modern Pentathlon will remain in the
Olympic programme in the next century, John Helmick, Olympic
attache of the International Union of Modern Pentathlon and
Biathlon (IUPMB), said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Modern pentathlon has a unique place because it is the only
sport that was organized specifically for the Olympics by the
international Olympic Committee," said Helmick.
</P>
<P>
The International Union of Modern Pentathlon and Biathlon
has introduced some changes in the organising of the Olympic
Modern Pentathlon championships.
</P>
<P>
"The athletes compete in all five events on one day while the
one day format has attracted various sponsors. We have great
improvement on the sport, on sponsors and on TV," Helmick said.
</P>
<P>
As a conclusion, Helmick emphasized: "Modern Pentathlon is an
important Olympic sport for the upcoming century. With the new
format, the Modern Pentathlon was the only sport that sold all
tickets for every session at the 1996 Olympic Games. No other
sport can do the same. I hope a sellout for all the tickets and
seats for the men's competitions as well as women's competitions
in the 2000 Olympics. That is the real goal for the Modern
Pentathlon." 
</P>
</TEXT>
