<HEADLINE> China's Transport Volume Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The latest Ministry of
Communications statistics show that 5.8 billion people travelled
by highway transportation during the first half of 1997, up 1.8
percent on the previous year's period.
</P>
<P>
The aggregate passenger transport volume rose 1.2 percent to
256.8 billion person/km, with the freight transport volume rising
by 1.5 percent to 4.79 billion tons.
</P>
<P>
Ministry statistics also show a slight 0.6 percent rise in the
inland maritime freight transport volume to 630 million tons, with
the passenger volume for water transportation falling 3.8 percent
to 109 million person times.
</P>
<P>
The volume of freight handled by major seaports jumped 5.1
percent to 420 million tons, including 4.24 million TEU
containers. The latter represented a 5.3 percent increase
on last year's same period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
