<DOCNO> XIE19970731.0281 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Expected to Have 2 Million Phone Lines by 2004 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will have at least 2
million telephone lines by the end of the seventh five-year
development plan in March 2004, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Based on official data, by March 1999, Indonesia will have some
11 million installed telephone lines for its 204 million
population.
</P>
<P>
The figure is expected to reach 21.5 million by the end of the
seventh five-year development plan for a population of some 219
million.
</P>
<P>
In 2009, an estimated 31 million lines are expected to be
installed for a 233 million population.
</P>
<P>
"The projection will be surpassed as we can use sophisticated
satellites to double telephone line installation, particularly in
rural areas," President of Pt. Pacific Satellite Nusantara (PDN)
Adi R. Adiwoso was quoted as saying here Wednesday.
There is a vast potential for market penetration in the rural
areas, where about 180 million people are living, said Adiwoso.
</P>
</TEXT>
