<HEADLINE> Panama To Sign Two Loan Contracts with World Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Panama will sign two loan
contracts totalling 50.5 million dollars with the World Bank,
the cabinet council said today.
</P>
<P>
The funds will serve to finance basic infrastructure projects
for the poor in the country, according to the council.
</P>
<P>
The first loan of 28 million dollars will be payable over 17
years with five years of grace at variable interest rates
calculated according to the policies established by the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
The second loan of 22.5 million dollars will be used to
fortify the National System of Protected Areas as well as for
the building of basic infrastructure for the poor.
</P>
<P>
This loan will be payable over 20 years beginning in the year
2002 with five years of grace. 
</P>
