<HEADLINE> Mexico's Foreign Reserves Reach 22.5 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Mexico's foreign reserves have
reached 22.5 billion U.S. dollars after increasing by 38 million
dollars last week, said the Banco de Mexico (Banxico).
</P>
<P>
However, Banxico, which serves as the country's central bank,
said its net international assets decreased by 13 million dollars
to nearly 15.2 billion dollars during the week of July 18-25.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures, it said, partly result from the state-owned
Mexican Petroleum Company's net outflow of 56 million dollars and
the Mexican federal government's net outflow of 31 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In addition, they reflect the gain of 74 million dollars from
the fluctuations in the exchange rates of the various currencies
that make up Banxico's international assets and liabilities.
</P>
