<HEADLINE> Beijing Rally Marks PLA Founding Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A grand rally is held here today
in the Great Hall of the People to mark the 70th anniversary of the
founding of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
The rally was sponsored by the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), the State Council and the Central
Military Commission (CMC).
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, the general secretary of the CPC Central
Committee, Chinese president and chairman of the CMC, delivered an
important speech.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China is witnessing an important historic
period of full-scale reform, opening-up and modernization drive in
advance of the rapidly approaching 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that "fulfilling our great targets and undertakings
related to safeguarding China's unity and security, while at the
same time promoting world peace and stability, requires us to
build a powerful army and consolidate national defense."
</P>
<P>
Jiang added that all members of the PLA must hold high
unswervingly the banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the armed forces to maintain a clear view of both
domestic and international situations, be vigilant in peace time,
strengthen their sense of responsibility and mission, and launch a
full-scale military development effort.
</P>
<P>
CMC Vice-Chairman Liu Huaqing, who is also a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Commmittee, presided over the gathering attended by Party and
government leaders Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Hu
Jintao and Rong Yiren.
</P>
<P>
By press time, the rally is still going on.  
</P>
</TEXT>
