<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China's Grain Production Threatened By Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The autumn grain output in
northeast China's Heilongjiang, Jilin and Liaoning provinces is
now threatened by a sustained drought this summer.
</P>
<P>
According to today's China Daily, some local rivers in the
three provinces have dried up for more than 40 days due to this
summer's long dry and hot weather there--the worst during the past
15 years.
</P>
<P>
In Jilin, the paper said, the rain fell between June 1 and July
21 was 43 percent less than the corresponding period last year and
16 percent less rainfall than in its worst ever drought 15 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
"Northeast China's severe drought will pose a serious threat to
the autumn grain crops scheduled for harvesting in about three
months if there is no rain in the next several weeks," the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, to date 12 million hectares of land
have been affected by the drought. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970731.0298 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia Becomes Top U.S. Aerospace Export Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Asia has supplanted Europe as
the top market for U.S. aerospace exports, which rose almost 20
percent in 1996 to 39.6 billion U.S. dollars, the Aerospace
Industries Association (AIA) said.
</P>
<P>
The increase in export sales covered civilian and military
products, said David Vadas, director of AIA's Research Center in
an analysis, according to the latest edition of the Defense News
weekly.
</P>
<P>
Vadas said, Aerospace sales in Asia accounted for about 13
percent of total industry sales and 41 percent of all exports,
while the sales to the European Union accounted for 39.7 percent
of all exports.
</P>
<P>
"The Asia-Pacific market is critical to the industry's
success... and it's ours to lose," he said. U.S. restrictions on
defense sales to China, Vietnam and other Asia Pacific nations
give a free hand to Russia, Vadas added.
</P>
<P>
According to AIA figures, the Middle East ranks third for U.S.
aerospace exports, with 7.2 percent of all export sales, followed
by Canada, 7 percent, Latin America, 4.1 percent, and Central
Europe, 0.6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970731.0299 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nation to Begin Rural Pilot Census </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The State Council has decided to
begin a pilot census in China's small towns and to tighten census
management in rural areas, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
State Council Secretary-General and State Councillor Luo Gan
said yesterday that the decision has been made in line with the
requirement for building socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Luo told a national teleconference yesterday that improving the
census in counties, townships and rural areas was important to
people's lives and was linked with economic development, social
progress and stability.
</P>
<P>
The changes were needed because in the last few years many
farmers have moved from the countryside to small towns in search
of work. The population shift has made the government's job of
providing social services difficult.
</P>
<P>
Under the new system, people who used to be farmers but are
currently working in pilot counties and townships can apply for
permanent residence in the small towns.
</P>
<P>
Those who have stable jobs and have lived at least two years in
the new areas can become permanent residents there.
</P>
<P>
This will help promote the orderly transfer of surplus rural
labor to small towns, ease population pressure on large- and
medium-sized cities and help modernize rural areas, Luo said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
