<HEADLINE> Menem To Attend Olympic Selection Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos
Menem will attend the ceremony to be held in Lausanne, Switzerland
on September 5 where the International Olympic Committee (IOC)
will select the city that will host the 2004 Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
It was announced by Tourism Minister Francisco Mayorga on
Wednesday. Mayorga explained that President Menem will be
accompanied by Fernando de la Rua, head of the Buenos Aires
municipal government and Sports Minister Hugo Porta.
</P>
<P>
Former Argentine tennis star Gabriela Sabatini will also attend
the gathering as a member of the IOC'S athlete's commission.
</P>
<P>
Mayorga said that a registration campaign is being held in
Buenos Aires for signing up volunteers in which they hope to get a
total of one million signatures supporting the city's nomination
which will be presented at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The other cities which are bidding to host the 2004 Olympic
Games are Stockholm, Rome, Athens and Capetown. 
</P>
