<HEADLINE> Greece Condemns Jerusalem Bombings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Greece today strongly condemned the
bombings in Jerusalem as "a terrorist act," saying that such acts
have a negative effect on the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Greek Foreign Ministry said in a statement that the people
and government of Greece condemned in the "most absolute way" and
express their abhorrence over today's terrorist act at the Mahane
Yehuda market in Jerusalem which killed at least 18 people and
injured over 150.
</P>
<P>
"Such acts have a negative effect on the Middle East peace
process, which is at a very delicate phase. The resumption of
negotiations as well as the promotion and completion of the peace
process can and must constitute the strong answer to terrorism,"
the statement said. 
