<HEADLINE> European Shares up, Frankfurt, Paris Hit New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe all
had a bullish day and surged strongly today, with Frankfurt and
Paris ending at new record closing highs, boosted by the Dow's
rally and the dollar's strength.
</P>
<P>
In London, Britain's leading FTSE 100 share index rose sharply
on Wall Street's overnight gains and a strong opening today, with
investors pouring into banking, oil and retail stocks. The FTSE
100 closed more than one percent up, or 50.7 points higher at
4,927.3.
</P>
<P>
However, dealers said they were still cautious ahead of a batch
of UK and US economic data.
</P>
<P>
On the Frankfurt market, German shares ended the session at a
new record closing high at 4,421.72, 40.3 points up, with trading
sentiment underpinned also by Wall Street's rally and the strong
dollar which helps the country's exporters.
</P>
<P>
French stocks followed Frankfurt's suit and finished at a new
record level, with the CAC-40 index at 3,069.30, 45.67 points
higher by the end of the session although below an all-time
intra-day trading high reached earlier in the day. 
</P>
